{
  "page": "Wolves in the Hills",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\"<b>Wolves in the Hills</b>\" is a song about the <a href=\"/index.php/Northern_mountains\" title=\"Northern mountains\">Northern mountains</a> and their inhabitants, the <a href=\"/index.php/Northern_mountain_clans\" title=\"Northern mountain clans\">Northern mountain clans</a>. Their liege lords, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Starks</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>, have often sent men into the mountains to settle feuds, which are remembered in songs such as \"Wolves in the Hills\" and \"<a href=\"/index.php/Black_Pines\" title=\"Black Pines\">Black Pines</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_mountain_clans.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_mountain_clans.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wolves_in_the_Hills&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_mountain_clans.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_mountain_clans.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The North: The Mountain Clans.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403122912\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic